column5: Bill and I are currently in the remote native  community of Kasabonika Lake waiting for a plane back to civilization. What a crazy adventure this past week has been! Can't wait to tell you guys the story. We fished a remote section of the Asheweig River, a giant trib of the Winisk with an Oji-Cree native. Perhaps the most memorable and eventful trip I've ever experienced...
Hey man....get back here now and tell us a all about it Have a safe trip back guys.
Crazy Adventure = OMG another awesome Borger report and I've been eagerly anticipating this one since you mentioned the Ashweig during the winter
Its gonna be good... i can just tell.
That does it! I'm not logging out 'til this report shows up.
